rComments: 3 weekly readings with a reading response that is only graded if you attend class! She is very well spoken and makes it easy to understand concepts. Assignments are marked relatively hard. The only thing is that there is a lot of group discussions, if you're an introvert you might not enjoy that. VERY heavy on readings for tests, cant ignore them!

I took a course with Brigid last summer and enjoyed it so much that I enrolled in another course of hers the following semester. She is passionate about what she teaches; she loves the subject matter and wants her students to do well. Very approachable and encouraging during office hours. Lots of assigned readings, some quite heavy. Overall a fave!
Burke is one of the best instructors I've had at U of T! she is very personable, cares about her students and helps the students with assignment and the material!
